    {
      "name": "vLLM",
      "kind": "serving-system",
      "last_reviewed": "2026-06-23",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.06180",
      "notes": "PagedAttention LLM serving engine (Kwon et al., SOSP 2023). Continuous / iteration-level batching + paged KV cache (~96% KV utilization, <4% waste); Automatic Prefix Caching (block-hash within-instance KV reuse, docs.vllm.ai/en/latest/features/automatic_prefix_caching); FP8 E4M3/E5M2 KV-cache dtype; XGrammar guided decoding; OpenAI-compatible server. The de facto open SOTA baseline this scorecard positions fak against on continuous batching, prefix caching, and the OpenAI API surface; the live gateway head-to-head is fak-fronts-vLLM vs raw-vLLM (the adjudication tax), the analog of the measured SGLang row."
